sentence: Larnelle Steward Harris (born July 6, 1947) is an American gospel singer and songwriter.
A native of Danville, Kentucky, Harris started playing the drums at the age of nine.
Perhaps Harris' best-known songs are his duets with Sandi Patty, "More than Wonderful" (1983) and "I've Just Seen Jesus" (1985).

Harris has received an honorary doctorate of music from Campbellsville University in central Kentucky.
Harris has appeared live on television series such as Live with Regis and Kathie Lee, The 700 Club, several Billy Graham crusades, and the Trinity Broadcasting Network.
In his hometown of Louisville, Kentucky, Harris has made many appearances on the WHAS Crusade for Children, a long-running local telethon benefitting children's charities.
Harris met his wife Cynthia (Mitzi) while both were students at Western Kentucky University.
They have two children Lonnie (Larnelle Jr.) and Teresa.
